Men. The paradox. The silent. The logical. The tyrant. The ever so often misunderstood. The recklessly loved and feared. The character that was forever missing from a parlour scene. Treading lightly on open greens. 
For the man that we’ve loved and found kind. For the man that we made divine. For the man that is forever on a climb. For the extraordinary. For the easy. And all that lies between them. 

Theater MAN. 
Stand strong.
